  "text": "Fine-grained reconfigurable logic for application improvement has been used for more than two decades. Early examples are the CEPRA-1X which was developed to speed up cellular automata simulations. It gained a speedup of more than 1000 compared with state of the art workstations [CITATION_1] . This level of speedup still persists for many application areas, for example, the BLAST algorithm [CITATION_2] . Unfortunately, these speedups require highly specialized HW architectures and domain specific modelling languages.",
